1070:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c **** /**
1071:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @brief  Select the Protection Mode (SPRMOD). 
1072:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * 
1073:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @note   This function can be used only for STM32F42xxx/43xxx and STM32F401xx/411xE devices.    
1074:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * 
1075:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @note   After PCROP activation, Option Byte modification is not possible. 
1076:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         Exception made for the global Read Out Protection modification level (level1 to level0)
1077:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @note   Once SPRMOD bit is active unprotection of a protected sector is not possible 
1078:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *   
1079:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @note   Read a protected sector will set RDERR Flag and write a protected sector will set WRPER
1080:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *   
1081:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @note   Some Precautions should be taken when activating the PCROP feature :
1082:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         The active value of nWRPi bits is inverted when PCROP mode is active, this means if SPR
1083:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         and WRPi = 1 (default value), then the user sector i is read/write protected.
1084:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         In order to avoid activation of PCROP Mode for undesired sectors, please follow the
1085:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         below safety sequence :       
1086:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         - Disable PCROP for all Sectors using FLASH_OB_PCROPConfig(OB_PCROP_Sector_All, DISABLE
1087:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *           for Bank1 or FLASH_OB_PCROP1Config(OB_PCROP_Sector_All, DISABLE) function for Bank2  
1088:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         - Enable PCROP for the desired Sector i using FLASH_OB_PCROPConfig(Sector i, ENABLE) fu
1089:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *         - Activate the PCROP Mode FLASH_OB_PCROPSelectionConfig() function. 
1090:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * 
1091:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @param  OB_PCROP:  Select the Protection Mode of nWPRi bits 
1092:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *          This parameter can be one of the following values:
1093:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *            @arg OB_PcROP_Disable: nWRPi control the write protection of respective user sectors
1094:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   *            @arg OB_PcROP_Enable: nWRPi control the  read&write protection (PCROP) of respective
1095:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   * @retval None
1096:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c ****   */
1097:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_flash.c **** void FLASH_OB_PCROPSelectionConfig(uint8_t OB_PcROP)
